    • Field Detail

      • FLAGS_CONNECT

        public static final int FLAGS_CONNECT
        Mask for the CONNECT bit, which indicates whether to draw a line segment from the previous vertex to the current vertex.

        Expressed as an int because bitwise operations with bytes are extremely error-prone in Java.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FLAGS_JOIN

        public static final int FLAGS_JOIN
        Mask for the JOIN bit, which indicates whether to use a join (e.g. miter) at the current vertex.

        Expressed as an int because bitwise operations with bytes are extremely error-prone in Java.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
